nd authorial voice as fleshy combinings of meaning and music.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aIntonation (Phonetics) 0aOral communicationxPhilosophy. 0aTranslating and interpretingxPhilosophy. 0aVoice in literature. 4aflesh. 4amusicality. 4aspeaking voice. 4aspoken word. 4avoice. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP / FUP eBook-Package 2016z978311071186840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823270026zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823270026423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823270026.jpg  a978-3-11-071186-8  NYUP / FUP eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK